diff --git a/docs/release-governance.md b/docs/release-governance.md
index ce7eb9816acff756a65e1d5ed9ddf8a48f2bf4d8..b9b278db5723d2edb730e0326f70eeac2f3340e2 100644
--- a/docs/release-governance.md
+++ b/docs/release-governance.md
@@ -63,3 +63,13 @@ The governance workflow regenerates the canonical override registry from the aud
 Tracked compiler caches, bytecode, temporary extraction directories, validation artefacts and build outputs are prohibited. The governance workflow runs with `PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1`, validates tracked paths before release attestation and uploads a separate hygiene report.
 
 The Release 235 cleanup removes thirteen accidentally tracked Python cache files. Full rollback uses `git revert`; the implementation patch intentionally does not recreate generated bytecode.
+
+## Release 236 repository integrity gate
+
+Release 236 completes the thirteen tracked-cache deletions that were not applied
+in Release 235. It adds a deterministic tracked-file inventory, required-asset
+checks, manifest-integrity checks, SARIF output, pre-commit enforcement and a
+dedicated Repository Integrity workflow.
+
+The release must be applied through Git. `APPLY_RELEASE_236.cmd` provides the
+recommended Windows path and applies the binary patch with `git apply --index`.
